import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['precipitation'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Precipitation')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temp_max'], label='Max Temperature')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temp_min'], label='Min Temperature')
    
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.title('How does temperature vary over time?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
